Ikoyi Club 1938 Ikoyi Club 1938 is set for a new era. The new dispensation, which begins today, is expected to usher in innovations that would once again show that golf is among the best ways of ensuring a healthy lifestyle. The new leadership of the club today unveil its programme for the next one year, ahead of its first major championship. According to feelers from the club, the newly elected committee, led by Dr. Innocent Meckson Okoro, has perfected plans for the Captain’s National Inaugural Tournament, tagged: Unity Cup Golf Championship 2021. The event will begin on March 25 with arrivals and practice round, with competition starting on March 26 with men of handicap 15 to 28, as well as ladies and veterans, guests with handicap 15 – 28. On March 27, men and guests with handicap 1 to 14 will take their turn before the gala dinner and awards sponsored by Polaris Bank. Speaking ahead of the first of its kind golf captain’s inaugural, Dr. Okoro, the new Captain assured of compliance with all COVID-19 protocols, while pleading for support from corporate organisations and members of the club, saying he needs their help to run the club well. “We are hoping for a very good year ahead of us. I also know that to succeed in this assignment, we will need the support of every member of the club and our corporate organisations, especially in the area of sponsorship of tournaments and Projects,” he said. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .